author: kiriny  ï¬∑·¥•¬∑  î
text:
signed in 2021 but the gym has went down in terms of quality and maintenance since then.
equipment maintenance:
- most of the steel plates are in shambles, rusty and coating chipped off (see pic)
- deadlift platform broken for some time (see pic), every time need to kick it back into position
- leg extension machine broke down a few times and took some time to be fixed only for it to be broken again
- machines rusty/ worn (see pic), attachments broken (see pic)

environment/ cleanliness
- locker area always smelling like sweat, very musty. can't stand there for long and my friends and i have to hold our breath there. personally i‚Äôve gagged a few times.
- washroom smells funky sometimes, found a dead roach as well.
- aircon is weak, dusty fans not helping (see pic), overall ventilation is poor
- not sure what‚Äôs going on with the walls (water stain, dust bunnies)

although cleanliness doesn‚Äôt affect your workout, it does bring down the overall ambience. it‚Äôs really a downer to work out in a gym where you can tell there isn‚Äôt much effort put into maintaining an okay environment for you. even if replacing worn equipment isn‚Äôt possible, the least that can be done is to maintain a clean environment for people who are paying ~$100 monthly.  other AFs have much better equipment maintenance, cleanliness, and general ambience yet charge the same price.

only coming here for convenience as it‚Äôs the nearest gym to me and to clock in my hours else my membership will be transferred to other AFs.

1 point cos i met a bunch of new friends here. community is not bad, lots of regular lifters and familiar faces.

hopefully management takes some form of action.

update Feb'24:
removed toilet paper from all cubicles to restrict usage, leaving only one roll outside for us to "take what we need". friends have mentioned they started locking up the toilets to restrict use as well.

notice all the 5 star reviews and how the accounts leaving them have 1-2 other reviews only? ü§î believe management gets them to leave good reviews when they sign up for some signup goodie bag

if there is a 0 star, i will give. i want to give -20 star but i cannot so 1 star.

text: Plan to sign up again but with the environmental review from others active gym members. To be honest its mind blowing. author: Alessander Fong
text:
have been a member at this place since they opened but decided  a few months ago to moved my homegym membership to another AF that deserves my monthly payment. Even though they 'refreshed' their place some months ago, it's just cosmetic wise looking better. equipment are still rusty and broken, nothing new at all. hygiene wise is one of the worst even seen in my life,

1)they don't even enforce people bringing their own towel. i have seen someone whose sweat stained singlet used the bench and just move to another workout with wiping.  told the staff on duty and they can only say they can't do anything.

2)they provide general towel and alcohol spray but the towel is one of the most disgusting one, towel is always damp and i have not seen them changing it to a new one at all for the longest time.

3)the final straw they broke was when they removed all the toilet papers and told the members to use bidet. hiding behind the name of 'environment friendly'(more like profit saving).paired this with the non enforcement of using towel. i have seen people leaving lump of stain on the bench after they left. no prize for guesting that this is likely to be after using the bidet and their private area are still wet, without any TP to dry then they used the bench for workout. i can't believe i was in Singapore. still come here due to the bigger space so give it 2*

you also should be seeing all the current 5* reviews with a few sentences? well they are giving some incentives for these reviews to jack up the rating. With all the new sign up, they have more than enough profit to do something to the gym but management just decided not to. if you are new please ask and plan to sign up with them, please ask them what are their hygiene policy and what equirement have they changed since their renovation.

text:
As a first-time gym-goer, I was inspired by my friends‚Äô positive experiences and decided to join Anytime Fitness (AF) Wisteria Mall. The newly renovated space is well-lit, perfectly air-conditioned, and very welcoming.

The staff, including Sagai Mary, Gillian, Trampoline class instructor Noor, and PT instructor Ben, made me feel right at home from the start.

A special shoutout to Sagai Mary! As the assistant manager, she was incredibly detailed and meticulous during my sign-up process. She wasn‚Äôt just professional but also warm and approachable, never pushing me into decisions. Her friendliness and genuine smile truly reflect the positive vibes at AF. Mary also went the extra mile to educate me on how to use the equipment, which boosted my confidence as a newbie.

Overall, it‚Äôs a 100/100 for AF Wisteria Mall from me! I highly recommend it to anyone :)

author: Kayla Tan
text:
just signed up not long ago , probs 1 month ago. i would just like to mention a few things. although this gym has 4 stars due to the reviews being placed when it was newly opened , the quality has dropped drastically. firstly , this af has one of the worst amenities i have seen in a gym. it is small , claustrophobic and has limited equipment , moreover , most of the equipment are either rusty or run-down and some of them are even out of order , making my experience very unpleasant. secondly , the staff here are terrible. on my first day at this af , i requested for a tour and a quick run down on how to use the machines. there was a malay male staff only which seemed extremely reluctant to do so , and when asked how to use the machines , he seemed condescending and was not patient even though i was obviously a beginner and wanted to genuinely learn. he left a terrible impression right away. thirdly , for a monthly payment of $95 , this is absolutely a huge scam , lack of machines and equipment , terrible staff members , musty smell at the bag area , it seemed to me like the staff couldnt give a care in the world at all. fourthly , i signed the contract with my full name written correctly and the agreement sent to me had my name mispelled , wrote an email to them asking them to change it. until now , there has been no amendments made. this is shocking as on my first few days at the gym , i frequently see that malay male staff sitting and looking at his monitor , so it makes no absolute sense why he couldnt reply to my email. i found this behaviour absolutely appalling. lastly , as a neighbourhood gym that is accessible for 24 hours and requires a monthly payment of $95 , this is atrocious considering the poor maintenance of the facility and the ignorant staff members. moreover , no cancellation within the period of signing up unless there is medical or relocation proof. this i felt was ridiculous. some people would obviously like to cancel the membership due to other reasons , perhaps they are busy with work and have no time to go the gym , and obviously they wouldnt want to pay $95 a month and waste it. as a consumer myself , the amenities in this gym are appalling considering the extremely high price point. the gym needs a major revamp in order to prove its worth. seriously , this is a scam. i would highly suggest anyone that is considering to sign up for af to think properly about it first before making rash decisions , staff members love to pursue you into signing up for memberships that cant be cancelled unless for some ridiculous reasons.
overall , this af is extremely not worth its monthly price and the amenities are absolute garbage.
plus , staff members really need to watch their attitude , especially that one malay male staff. gave me the impression that he didnt feel like working anymore , which i feel would be for the better , since his attitude and body language was revolting.
